cs.CL, cs.SD, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely category as the paper deals with natural language processing and specifically focuses on grapheme-to-phoneme conversion using neural models. 
- cs.SD (Sound) is also a likely category as the paper deals with phonemes and their conversion from graphemes. 
- cs.LG (Learning) is another possible category as the paper proposes a new model for learning to align and convert characters to phonemes. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper uses neural models for the task of grapheme-to-phoneme conversion. 
- cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible category as the paper proposes a neural model for the task.
